- The integer array parameter `grid` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `grid` must represent a map where `grid[i][j] = 1` represents land and `grid[i][j] = 0` represents water.
- The integer array parameter `grid` must be completely surrounded by water.
- There is exactly one island in the `grid`.
- The island in the `grid` doesn't have "lakes".
- The perimeter of the island must be determined.
- The integer result is the perimeter of the island.
- The perimeter is calculated by counting the number of yellow stripes in the image.
- The width and height of the grid do not exceed 100.
- The length of the integer array parameter `grid` is equal to the number of rows.
- The length of each row in the integer array parameter `grid` is equal to the number of columns.